# What are the ongoing efforts to confirm Christian Atsu's condition and whereabouts after the conflicting reports?

## Summary
Earlier, reports had claimed that Christian Atsu, a Ghanaian soccer star, had been rescued from a building's rubble that collapsed due to an earthquake in southern Turkey <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. However, these reports were contradicted by Atsu's agent, Nana Sechere, who stated on Twitter that Atsu's whereabouts were still unknown <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font><font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. The agent further emphasized the severity of the situation and the ongoing efforts to locate Atsu <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font><font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. Prior to this, Sechere had informed CNN that Atsu was in a "stable" condition in a local hospital after being rescued <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font><font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. The Ghana Football Association also confirmed Atsu's rescue and stable condition <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. Meanwhile, Volkan Demirel, the manager of Hatayspor, the team Atsu plays for, reported to Reuters that the search for Atsu was still ongoing with no new updates <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

